==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''adducere'', ''adductum'', to lead or bring to; ''ad'' + ''ducere'' to lead. See [[Duke]], and [[cf.]] [[Adduct]].] 

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-uːs|-uːs]]

===Transitive Verb===

#To bring forward or offer, as an argument, passage, or consideration which bears on a statement or case; to cite; to allege.
#:*Reasons ... were '''adduced''' on both sides. - ''[[Macaulay]]''.
#:*Enough could not be adduced to satisfy the purpose of illustration. - ''[[De Quincey]]''.

